===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|䰜|米|ls=ic|t1=cauldron|t2=rice}} — congee. Original form of {{och-l|粥|congee}}.

{{och-l|*䰜}} is a variant form of {{zh-l|*鬲}}, which is a cauldron with three hollow legs, in which {{zh-l|*米|rice}} is cooked. The two {{lang|zh|弓}} depict the steam emitted from the congee in the cauldron.

{{zh-l|*粥|congee}} is a reduced form of {{lang|zh|鬻}}. {{lang|zh|鬻}} has since been {{Han phonetically borrowed}} to represent {{och-l|𧶠|to sell}}.

===Etymology===
; "to sell"
: Compare {{cog|km|លក់||to sell; to fine}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). May not be related to {{och-l|贖|to redeem}}.

